        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:41PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Taylorsville, or 10
miles southwest of Cartersville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cartersville, Acworth, Rockmart, Euharlee, Emerson, Braswell,
Taylorsville, Cross Roads, Burnt Hickory Ridge, Stilesboro, and Red
Top Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
